        "So that's what they are wearing in Huge Kingdom nowadays." I joked as I watched Ken maneuver his character around a grassy, mountainous landscape.  <br/><br/>Ken was shadowing a character resembling a minotaur, straight out of mythology.  <br/><br/>The minotaur was, by definition, a half-human and half-creature character wearing not a single piece of wardrobe.  <br/><br/>"We're in hot pursuit! Guh guh guh!" Scrap joked in his best Rosco P. Coltraine impersonation.<br/><br/>Sometimes I just want to smack Scrap."We got a hot tip from another player in the game about this minotaur character named 'trotsky'" Ken said as he panned around the area.  The minotaur was in the middle of killing several small monster-type characters using some sort of magical flash.<br/><br/>"Lady luck is favoring us today it would seem." I thought to myself.<br/><br/>"Ken, where exactly did this tip come from, and what did they say?" I asked.<br/><br/>"A player that was killed by trotsky sent an email to our support address and reported him.  Apparently trotsky approached him in the game and was trying to arrange some sort of a sale involving level 50 magical powers." Ken said as he zoomed in on the minotaur.  "To make matters even more interesting, trotsky is one of many names this player has used.  His first two names 'lightbringer' and 'godofdeath' should ring a bell with you."<br/><br/>I thought for a moment.  "Holy half-price mochas... those are two of the character names that showed up on those exception reports." I exclaimed.  "Is he aware that you're following him around?" <br/><br/>"I don't think so.  The character I'm playing as is actually a 'debug' character that isn't viewable to other players.  We use these players to troubleshoot problems all the time." Ken informed us.  "I'm not sure why I didn't think of doing this before."<br/><br/>I watched the screen intently.  No matter how many cases I work on, I always learn something new, aside from the many fine Starbucks locations around the country.<br/><br/>"Are you thinking what I'm thinking?" Scrap asked me, his eyes still lit up like the burning cherry of a half-smoked Newport.<br/><br/>"Well, we're not at a strip club, so I'm going to say yes.  Sting operation." I replied with a grin.  "This works well for drug deals, why not cyber-ware deals?  Ken, can you 'un-cloak' your character at some point and approach trotsky?"<br/><br/>"Hell yeah." Ken said.  "You want me to do it now?"<br/><br/>"Not right now.  Let's treat this as surveillance for a while and take some notes on his behavior." I said as I flipped the page of my notepad.<br/><br/>An hour and a few slices of pizza later, we caught a break.  Trotsky approached another player.<br/><br/>"No need for hidden microphones in this game." Ken joked as he hit a key on the keyboard.  A transparent console scrolled down over the screen.  Ken entered a few debug commands and balloons appeared over the players' heads.<br/><br/>"That is frick'in cool!" Scrap boomed as he moved in for a closer look.  I tried to read the balloons and make some notes at the same time.<br/><br/><i><br/>Trotsky: "Have you found the 'Sword of Summoning' yet?"<br/><br/>Player: "Hell no, I'm not even through my second quest yet."<br/><br/>Trotsky: "I have one for sale.  Interested?"<br/><br/>Player: "I have only 200 gold pieces."<br/><br/>Trotsky: "How much cash do you have?"<br/><br/>Player: "???"<br/><br/>Trotsky: "It's for sale on eBay.  My id is 'hugekingdomwares'."<br/><br/>Player: "You can do that?"<br/><br/>Trotsky: "Well, I can.  I'll prove it right now."<br/><br/>Player: "ok"<br/></i><br/><br/>Both characters stood motionless.<br/><br/>"Scrap, is the equipment in place?" I asked as I poked Scrap's arm.<br/><br/>"Huh? Uh, oh it's plugged in.  Crap I didn't turn capturing on!" Scrap cried as he ran for the operations center.<br/><br/>Balloons appeared over the characters' heads once again.<br/><br/><i><br/>Trotsky: "Check out your gold."<br/><br/>Player: "Woah! I have 2000 gold pieces."<br/><br/>Trotsky: "Maybe we can make  a deal?"<br/></i><br/><br/>I was about to make Trotsky an offer that he couldn't refuse.
    </div>    
    <div class="spacer"></div>
    <div class="marginleftgutter">
